oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Planting grass after the corn
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Estry, D.H., photographer
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: 1948 cornfield in which twelve pounds of Ky.31 fescue and two pounds of ladino clover, per acre, were broadcast. Seeded for rotation pasture - classes two and three land.

One in a series of photographs of agricultural activities in Cannon County, TN that were taken by W.L. Clement, District Conservationist for the U.S. Soil Conservation Service, and his assistants between the mid-1940s and mid-1970s.
